This paper deals with modal logic and its algebraic semantics, which are topics that are commonly studied in the computer science subfield of logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the extension of a modal logic system, which is a topic that is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new framework for algebraic semantics, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). Furthermore, the paper discusses the axioms of propositional identity, which are relevant to the subfield of programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the containment relationships between different modal logic systems, which is a topic that is relevant to the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC).
